<slide bg="linen" fg="black">
<text align="c" xp="50" yp="90" sp="4.5" >Aristotle's Rhetorical Triangle</text>
<text type="block" xp="5" yp="75" wp="30" sp="2" >Aristotle thought that a speaker's ability to persuade an audience is based on how well the speaker appeals to them through</text>
<polygon xc="45 65 85" yc="30 80 30" color="black" opacity="30"/>
<text align="c" xp="65" yp="80" sp="2.5" font="sans" color="rgb(70,130,180)">ETHOS</text>
<text align="e" xp="45" yp="30" sp="2.5" font="sans" color="#dc143c">LOGOS</text>
<text xp="85" yp="30" sp="2.5" font="sans" color="#00aa00">PATHOS</text>
<list type="bullet" xp="5" yp="50" sp="2" >
<li font="sans" color="rgb(70,130,180)">ETHOS: Ethics (Credibility)</li>
<li font="sans" color="#00aa00">PATHOS: Emotion (Feeling)</li>
<li font="sans" color="#dc143c">LOGOS: Logic (Data)</li>
</list>
<text type="block" xp="5" yp="15" wp="80" sp="2" font="serif">Du Bois developed a sociological framework to show Black Americans are capable of functioning as social equals, social Darwinism has no data to back its theory.</text>
